What is E91 Entanglement-Based QKD?
E91 is a quantum key distribution (QKD) protocol proposed by Artur Ekert (1991).
It uses quantum entanglement to allow two parties (Alice and Bob) to generate a shared secret key in a provably secure way.
In an E91 Qiskit demo, this protocol is simulated using Qiskit to show how entangled qubits can be used to create secure keys and detect eavesdropping.

Why is E91 used?
